The paper deals with the complexity of pattern matching, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The k-mismatch problem is a well-studied problem in this area, and the paper presents new algorithms for both the offline and streaming versions of the problem. The algorithms involve techniques from data structures, algorithms, and information theory, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DM, cs.IT, and cs.LG. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
